
Creating HTML templates for a user management system for a hotel management project involves several key pages. Here's a basic outline for key templates:
1-Login Page (login.html): For users to log into the system.
2-Dashboard Page (dashboard.html): The main page where users can see various options like managing rooms, bookings, or users.
3-User List Page (user-list.html): Displays the list of users (admin and guests) with options to add, update, or delete users.
4-Add User Page (add-user.html): Form to add a new user (admin, guest).
5-Edit User Page (edit-user.html): Form to update existing user details.
6-Room Management Page (rooms.html): Manage hotel rooms (view, add, or modify room details).

1. Login Page (login.html)

     <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Login - Hotel Management</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="login-container">
        <h2>Hotel Management Login</h2>
        <form action="dashboard.html" method="POST">
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="username">Username</label>
                <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="password">Password</label>
                <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required>
            </div>
            <button type="submit">Login</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

2. Dashboard Page (dashboard.html)

       <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dashboard - Hotel Management</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="dashboard-container">
        <h1>Welcome to Hotel Management Dashboard</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="user-list.html">User Management</a></li>
                <li><a href="rooms.html">Room Management</a></li>
                <li><a href="bookings.html">Booking Management</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </div>
</body>
</html>



        3. User List Page (user-list.html)

         <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>User Management - Hotel</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="user-list-container">
        <h2>User Management</h2>
        <a href="add-user.html">Add New User</a>
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>ID</th>
                    <th>Username</th>
                    <th>Email</th>
                    <th>Role</th>
                    <th>Actions</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>1</td>
                    <td>admin</td>
                    <td>admin@example.com</td>
                    <td>Admin</td>
                    <td>
                        <a href="edit-user.html?id=1">Edit</a> | 
                        <a href="#">Delete</a>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <!-- More users can be listed here -->
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</body>
</html>


          4. Add User Page (add-user.html)

               <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Add User - Hotel Management</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="add-user-container">
        <h2>Add New User</h2>
        <form action="user-list.html" method="POST">
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="username">Username</label>
                <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="email">Email</label>
                <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="role">Role</label>
                <select id="role" name="role" required>
                    <option value="admin">Admin</option>
                    <option value="guest">Guest</option>
                </select>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="password">Password</label>
                <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required>
            </div>
            <button type="submit">Add User</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>



         5. Edit User Page (edit-user.html)

            <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Edit User - Hotel Management</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="edit-user-container">
        <h2>Edit User</h2>
        <form action="user-list.html" method="POST">
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="username">Username</label>
                <input type="text" id="username" name="username" value="admin" required>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="email">Email</label>
                <input type="email" id="email" name="email" value="admin@example.com" required>
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
                <label for="role">Role</label>
                <select id="role" name="role" required>
                    <option value="admin">Admin</option>
                    <option value="guest">Guest</option>
                </select>
            </div>
            <button type="submit">Update User</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>



          6. Room Management Page (rooms.html)

              <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Room Management - Hotel</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="rooms-container">
        <h2>Manage Hotel Rooms</h2>
        <a href="add-room.html">Add New Room</a>
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Room Number</th>
                    <th>Type</th>
                    <th>Price</th>
                    <th>Status</th>
                    <th>Actions</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>101</td>
                    <td>Deluxe</td>
                    <td>$150</td>
                    <td>Available</td>
                    <td>
                        <a href="edit-room.html?id=101">Edit</a> | 
                        <a href="#">Delete</a>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <!-- More rooms can be listed here -->
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
</body>
</html>


         Common Styles (styles.css)

             body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

h1, h2 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.container {
    width: 80%;
    margin: auto;
}

.input-group {
    margin: 10px 0;
}

label {
    display: block;
    font-weight: bold;
}

input, select {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 8px;
    margin-top: 5px;
}

button {
    padding: 10px 15px;
    background-color: #007bff;
    color: white;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}

button:hover {
    background-color: #0056b3;
}

table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
}

table, th, td {
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
}

th, td {
    padding: 10px;
    text-align: center;
}


            


          

        

     
   
      
